The paper discusses the use of pairwise constraints in machine learning and pattern recognition, which are common topics in several sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on propagation techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language), and security, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
